AU  - Ahmad G. Shtayyat
AU  - Mohammad AlShaikh Hasan
AB  - The convergence of cybersecurity insurance and artificial intelligence creates opportunities and challenges for risk assessment professionals. As cyber threats grow exponentially, traditional risk analysis models prove inadequate, necessitating professionals with advanced AI-driven analytical capabilities. This chapter examines educational frameworks needed to prepare future cybersecurity insurance experts for AI-enhanced risk analysis. Through expert review of current methodologies, educational design models, and industry best practices, we identify critical competency gaps and propose comprehensive solutions. Key findings indicate effective programs must balance technical AI literacy with specialized insurance knowledge, grounded in ethical considerations and regulatory compliance. The proposed framework encompasses undergraduate foundational curricula, specialized graduate programs, and continuous professional development to address diverse career trajectories within cybersecurity insurance.
