AU  - Pierre Picard
AB  - AbstractWe characterize the design of insurance schemes when policyholders face several insurable risks in a context of adverse selection. Splitting risks emerges as a feature of second‐best Pareto optimality. This may take the form of risk‐specific contracts, or of contracts where risks are bundled but subject to differential coverage rules, such as risk‐specific copayments combined with a deductible or a cap on coverage.
