AB  - AbstractProperty‐casualty (P&amp;C) claim reserves are financial statement liabilities that represent estimated future claims. An understanding of P&amp;C reserves is important to both risk managers and investment analysts, since this information is crucial in assessing solvency and value. We review some basics of P&amp;C reserves, and add some of our own thoughts, in a way that tries to be user‐friendly for practitioners and students.
